Lorica is a fork of Pingora, modified to serve as a dashboard-first
reverse proxy product. The original Pingora source code has been
renamed from pingora-* to lorica-*, with unused components removed
(OpenSSL, BoringSSL, s2n-tls backends, cache subsystem).

Architectural patterns in Lorica are inspired by Sozu (Clever Cloud),
reimplemented from scratch. No Sozu code has been copied (AGPL-3.0
prevents code reuse).

GeoIP data
----------

When the GeoIP country filter (v1.4.0) is enabled and the operator
does not override `GlobalSettings.geoip_db_path`, Lorica's automatic
update task downloads the IP-to-Country Lite database published by
DB-IP.com.

  "IP to Country Lite" by DB-IP.com is licensed under
  CC-BY-4.0 (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/).
  Source: https://db-ip.com/db/download/ip-to-country-lite

Operators that redistribute a Lorica binary or an image with the
pre-loaded database MUST preserve the above attribution in their
own NOTICE / README. The `.mmdb` file format is compatible with
MaxMind's GeoLite2, so operators with a MaxMind license can opt out
of the DB-IP source by pointing `geoip_db_path` at their own file
and disabling `geoip_auto_update_enabled`.

Dashboard world-map asset
-------------------------

The country-picker widget on the dashboard Protection tab bundles
the SVG world map file at `lorica-dashboard/frontend/src/assets/
world-map.svg`, which is a derivative of the Wikimedia Commons
"BlankMap-World" file published by user "Canuckguy" (and successive
contributors).

  "BlankMap-World.svg" is licensed under Creative Commons
  Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 Unported (CC BY-SA 3.0,
  https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/).
  Source: https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:BlankMap-World.svg

Operators redistributing a Lorica binary or image MUST preserve this
attribution. The map is only used to render a country picker; no
derivative of it appears in proxied traffic. If the CC BY-SA
attribution requirement is incompatible with your redistribution,
delete `lorica-dashboard/frontend/src/assets/world-map.svg` before
building the dashboard — the picker component falls back to a plain
text input on a missing asset.
